<ce:para>In this paper, we consider functions of the form φ(x, y) = f (x)g(y) over a box, where f (x), x ε. ℝ is a nonnegative monotone convex function with a power or an exponential form, and g(y), y ε. ℝ <sup>n</sup> is a component-wise concave function which changes sign over the vertices of its domain. We derive closed-form expressions for convex envelopes of various functions in this category.We demonstrate via numerical examples that the proposed envelopes are significantly tighter than popular factorable programming relaxations. © Springer Science+Business Media, LLC. 2011.</ce:para>
